description:
JL Mast is a layout artist for Marvel digital line: the Infinite Comics.

He worked on the series:

"Avengers Millennium",

"Guardians of the Galaxy Infinite",

"Amazing Spider-Man: Who Am I?",

"Avengers Assemble Infinite"

"Ultimate Spider-Man Infinite",

"Iron Man: Fatal Frontier",

"Thanos A God Up There Listening"

"Captain America Fear Him:"

"Original Sin: Secret Avengers"...

JL Mast is also the co-creator of Pax Arena & The Walking Pandas, published by Mark Waid's Thrillbent. He was the co-cartoonist of Jim The Duck's comic strips, from NBC's famous TV show Community.
name: J. L. Mast

description:
Leonardo Gonzalez is an artist and illustration it is his career of choice. Originally from Ridgewood Queens, Leo now resides in Connecticut where he lives with his girlfriend and tons of animals. He’s a Graduate from the University of Hartford with a degree in Illustration and also earned an Associates Degree in Fine Arts at Tunxis Community College.

In college Leonardo was pursuing a career in the comics field and after attending many New York Comic-Con Conventions he was hired as a cover and interior illustrator by U.K Comics Publisher T- Publications .

He is currently illustrating “THEATRICS” a new Graphic novel written by Neil Gibson to be published by T-Publications in 2017. Aside from comics Leo also creates whimsical illustrations that focus on nature, creatures, monsters and ghouls.
name: Leonardo Gonzalez

description:
Melvin S. Calingo is also known as Taga-Ilog. He is a comics writer and illustrator as well as a director of animated short films.

He is currently writing and illustrating the post apocalyptic action-drama Pasig for Culture Crash Comics in the Philippines.
name: Melvin Calingo

deck: Writer, artist and designer of graphic novels.
description:
He grew up with Comics, Bruce Lee flicks and Soul music of '66/'76. Ameziane (not yet Amazing...) worked several years in the magazine and the Advertisement business as Art Director, illustrator and graphic designer. Late 2001, he finally kickstart his comicbook career by writing several scripts. CLAN was the first one, but it would be to be published several years later... 13 years later exactly. In the meantime, he work also on the comics adaptation of the novel "CUATRO MANOS" with PACO IGNACIO TAIBO 2, his favorite novelist. He couldn't be more happy.

Now Amazing, Ameziane share his time between his books with TAIBO and the ones with Sybille Titeux and his own crime stories comics. Ameziane wrote several movie scripts, the first one in prodcution is the adaptation of one of his books. And of course, he doesn't sleep enough...

Bibliography (selection)
In english
- "MUHAMMAD ALI" with Sybille titeux - Dark Horse Comics (2016)

in France
- "CUATRO MANOS" with Paco Ignacio Taibo 2 - EP (2006)
- "BAGMEN" - Casterman (2013)
- " CLAN" - Lombard (2015)
- "MUHAMMAD ALI" (2015)
- "SAM HICKS (2017)
name: Amazing Ameziane
